body:
The problem is because of missing `\` which is of course wrong in the library, but it worked before version 2.0.39 it seems.

Does not work:

```php
class TestValidator extends Validator
{
    public function __construct(yii\httpclient\Request $httpClientRequest = null, $config = [])
    {
        parent::__construct($config);
    }
}
```

works:

```php
class TestValidator extends Validator
{
    public function __construct(\yii\httpclient\Request $httpClientRequest = null, $config = [])
    {
        parent::__construct($config);
    }
}
```

And run, inside a controller or i with Yii::createObject:

```php
class TestController extends \luya\web\Controller
{
    public function actionIndex()
    {
        $model = (new DynamicModel(['foo']))
            ->addRule('foo', TestValidator::class);

        $model->load([]);
    }
}
```

Yes indeed, the above code worked with yii version 2.0.38 and below.
